SC Verdict on Aadhar a big win for Modi Govt’s anti-black money efforts
SC has  upheld Section 139AA(1) which mandatorily requires quoting of Aadhaar for new PAN applications as well as for filing of returns.
SC also upheld Section 139AA(2) which requires that Aadhaar number must be intimated to prescribed authority 4 purpose of linking with PAN
Thus, Every person eligible to obtain Aadhaar must quote their Aadhaar number 4 filing of income tax returns as well as 4 applications 4 PAN
Thus,Everyone who has been allotted PAN & who has Aadhaar no. or is eligible to obtain Aadhaar number,shall have 2 link his PAN with Aadhaar
This is yet another vindication of Modi Govt’s efforts against corruption & black money from the top court of the country.
This move will prove to be a major help to fight corruption, black money and illegitimate financial transactions
